18/10/2005
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A court in Banja Ljuka acquitted on Monday (17 October) former Republika Srpska (RS) Prime Minister Milorad Dodik and former RS Finance Minister Novak Kondic of misappropriations charges.
The two had been accused of abuse of office and negligence in public work during their mandates from 1998-2000.
In its verdict, the court cited a lack of evidence.
(Nezavisne novine - 18/10/05;
RTRS, Fena - 17/10/05)
